Mandatory semantic versioning lesson:
12.0.0 means they have released a new MAJOR version.

in semantic versioning it goes like: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
where major is, well major changes (creates incompatability with previous versions)
MINOR is usually small feature updates
PATCH is bug fixes

And that's why they "had to have that extra 0"
